**Tests:** none — docs-only planning notes, no code path. Verify by: re-reading
both docs to confirm (a) the four lenses are defined compactly with evidence
requirements, (b) the seat→role paragraph does not frame model identity as the
mechanism, (c) the every-seat-all-lenses decision is stated with rationale,
(d) each PRESERVE constraint has an explicit "kept" line, (e) no P1-P4 or
defect-class rationale was deleted, (f) the prompt template's lens block composes
with the existing GO/BLOCK contract. No `make docs`/`make reconcile` needed
(non-generated planning notes).

**Docs:** this bead IS the docs change. No separate user-facing doc or generated
command reference is affected (the runbook/process docs are internal planning
notes under docs/plans/dogfood/, not the generated CLI reference). No
docs-reality/reconcile impact.

**Risks:**
- Bloat risk — the goal is to REDUCE load, so the new section must stay compact
  (≈the four lenses + evidence, ~25-35 lines) and rely on cross-references rather
  than restating the defect classes. Mitigation: the active layer is additive but
  SMALL; the bulk stays as reference. The gate (Spec Adversary lens on its own
  acceptance) should check the section is genuinely compact, not another page of
  prose.
- Terminology collision with `reviewed_stages[].role` — mitigated by the explicit
  "lens, not schema role" note and "review lenses" titling.
- Boundary drift with 8hq.7 — mitigated by the explicit boundary section above.

